This is complicated as the [example](https://codyhouse.co/demo/schedule-template/index.html) you provided is complex. However, I can give you some tips to create an html table using data from Sheets:

You can get the data of each cell with the [getValues()](https://developers.google.com/apps-script/reference/spreadsheet/range#getValues()) method. This generates a 2D array (rows and cloumns of the table). For example:

`var values = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSheet().getRange(&quot;A1:F11&quot;).getValues();`

Then you can nest a `for` loop inside another to generate a string containing the html code and the values of the table:
```
var htmlString = &#39;&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body&gt;&#39;;
for (var i = 0; i &lt; values[0].length; i++){
    
    htmlString += &#39;&lt;tr&gt;&#39;+values[i];
    
    for (var j = 0; j &lt; values.length; j++){
           
        htmlString += &#39;&lt;th&gt;&#39;+values[j][i]+&#39;&lt;/th&gt;&#39;;
    }
   
    htmlString += &#39;&lt;/tr&gt;&#39;;
}
 htmlString += &#39;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;&#39;
```

